<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf692553f-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s11504"><num value="11504">§ 11504.</num><heading> Enforcement of forfeitures</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">When an offense by a seaman also is a criminal violation, it is not necessary that a criminal proceeding be brought to enforce a forfeiture.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf6925540-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/584">97 Stat. 584</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
